To create a Discord bot using Discord.js v14 with a single slash command "ban", follow these steps:

1. First, make sure you have Node.js and npm installed on your computer. If you don't have them, download and install them from the official website: <https://nodejs.org/en/>

2. Create a new folder for your bot and open a terminal or command prompt in that folder.

3. Run the following command to create a new Discord bot and get the bot token:

```
npm init discord.js
```

4. This command will prompt you to answer a few questions. Answer them as follows:

* bot name: MyBanBot
* bot description: A simple bot with a ban command
* bot version: 1.0.0
* bot invite URL: https://discord.com/oauth2/authorize?client_id=YOUR_CLIENT_ID&scope=bot
* bot token: YOUR_BOT_TOKEN

Replace YOUR_CLIENT_ID and YOUR_BOT_TOKEN with your actual values.

5. After running the command, you will find a new folder called "MyBanBot" with the following files:

* package.json
* index.js
* package-lock.json

6. Open the "index.js" file in a text editor and replace its content with the following code:

```
const { SlashCommandBuilder } = require("discord.js");

module.exports = {
  data: new SlashCommandBuilder()
    .setName("ban")
    .setDescription("Bans a member from the server.")
    .addUserOption((option) =>
      option.setName("user").setDescription("The user to ban.")
    )
    .addIntegerOption((option) =>
      option.setName("days").setDescription("The number of days to delete messages for.")
    ),
  async execute(interaction) {
    const user = interaction.options.getUser("user");
    const days = interaction.options.getInteger("days");

    if (!interaction.member.permissions.has("BAN_MEMBERS")) {
      return interaction.reply({
        content: "You do not have the required permissions to use this command.",
        ephemeral: true,
      });
    }

    if (!user) {
      return interaction.reply({
        content: "Please provide a user to ban.",
        ephemeral: true,
      });
    }

    await interaction.guild.members.ban(user, { days });
    interaction.reply({
      content: `Successfully banned ${user.username}.`,
      ephemeral: true,
    });
  },
};
```

7. Save the file and run the following command to start your bot:

```
node index.js
```

Your bot is now online and ready to use the "ban" slash command. To use the command, open your Discord server and type "/ban" followed by the user you want to ban and the number of days to delete messages for.

Note: Make sure to replace YOUR_CLIENT_ID and YOUR_BOT_TOKEN with your actual values in the "index.js" file. Also, make sure to invite your bot to your server using the invite URL generated in step 4.

